    "encrypted": "false",
    "long_instructions": "## Do This:\r\n\r\n1. Import your `custom.py` into your project.\r\n\r\n*Don't have it, or it doesn't work? That's ok! Copy the code from* <a href=\"https://studio.code.org/projects/pythonlab/lEeO0M85P_A_B2Jcx0d2yC2yibkCG10AF_gD4ioh5Ws/view\" target=\"_blank\">***here***</a> *and paste it into a new file in your project.*\r\n\r\n2. In `custom.py`, write the `collect_paint(this_painter)` function. Inside this function:\r\n\r\n   * Use a `while` loop so the `Painter` moves forward until it can't anymore.\r\n\r\n   * Inside the loop, use an `if` statement to check if it is on a bucket.\r\n\r\n   * If it is, call your `take_all_paint(this_painter)` function to collect the paint.\r\n\r\n3. Save `custom.py` to your Backpack.\r\n\r\n4. In `main.py`, import your functions.\r\n\r\n```\r\nfrom custom import function_name, function_name, function_name\r\n```\r\n\r\n5. Use your functions to collect the paint from all the paint buckets.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n![](https://images.code.org/cc5f5ff89b4c4e3e1601197354c22a20-choiceA.gif)\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n<i class=\"fa-solid fa-laptop\"></i> **Coding Tip**\r\n\r\nUse the UMPIRE strategy to help you program this solution:\r\n\r\n* **U**nderstand: What's the goal? What conditional statement do I need? \r\n\r\n* **M**ake a plan: What expression will go in the conditional statement?\r\n\r\n* **P**roduce: Create the conditional statement.\r\n\r\n* **I**nspect: Run it -- does it work as expected?\r\n\r\n * **R**efine: Revise your code as needed.\r\n\r\n* **E**xplain: How did using a conditional statement make your program work as needed?",
